As Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Dangote Group, Aliko Dangote, turns 65 today, President Muhammadu Buhari has sent words of felicitations to him. Buhari, who conveyed his message through his media aide, Femi Adesina, on Sunday, said he joins family members, friends and associates to celebrate the milestone of the business magnate. On the occasion of the birthday commemorated on April 10, Buhari said he can affirm the footprints of the businessman in key sectors of the economy. He also commended him for building Africa’s largest refinery, fertiliser manufacturing company, and cement factories. “The President wishes him greater service to God, country, and humanity,” the Presidential spokesman added on behalf of his principal.